grant program by the Stella
and Charles Guttman Foundation, Inc., of New York.
The college will receive $5,000 annually for the next four
years to be used to defeat all
or part of tuition or comprehensive fees for as many students as the college choices.
Terms of the grant specify
that the scholarships be award<
ed on a basis of financial need,
with preference given to students in the junior and senior
years who are contamination
graduate or professional study.
 
